ive but doesnt hurt ;-)<br />&gt; &gt; <br />&gt; <br />&gt; I think what we need to do is to test the NOPL instruction and create a<br />&gt; Linux-specific CPUID bit for it.  I'll do that and submit to tip:x86/cpu.<br /><br />I also suspect that we'd really be much better off just fixing the generic <br />NOP tables for the 5-byte nop. As far as I could tell, from all the <br />numbers that have been posted, absolutely _none_ show that there is any <br />point at all to the 2-instruction 3/2-byte sequence.<br /><br />So instead of having a magic special ftrace-only thing, why not just do it <br />right, and fix the generic 5-byte nop sequence?<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
